Systematic Active U.S. Core Equity Program 
        
        
        










	Asset Management: Strategic Investment Division (“SID”)

	The Strategic Investment Division (“SID”) provides asset management services to private investment funds, separate accounts (such as pension funds and insurance companies) and other institutional investors with over $1 billion in assets under management.  SID is a division of Jefferies Investment Advisers, LLC, a SEC Registered Investment Adviser (RIA), CFTC registered Commodity Trading Advisor (CTA) and member of the NFA.

	The investment programs employed by SID are all fully systematic and cover multiple styles, strategies, asset-classes, geographies and time horizons.  Diversification is a hallmark of SID’s approach.  The SID team adheres to a rigorous research process utilizing the latest technology to apply the scientific method to alpha discovery, development and innovation. 

	SID manages risk systematically across all its programs and trades electronically to maximize efficiency and minimize slippage and alpha decay.   
















