About Us - Jefferies LoanCore LLC

























 









 

About Us

Jefferies LoanCore LLC (JLC) was formed in February 2011 as a joint venture among an affiliate of Jefferies Group LLC (www.jefferies.com), an affiliate of GIC Real Estate (GIC RE), the real estate investment arm of Government of Singapore Investment Corporation, and members of management.  JLC originates commercial real estate debt through a team of professionals led by Mark Finerman. This long-term equity investment in JLC supports a $2.8 billion plus capital base directed toward new mortgage funding.
JLC was formed to capitalize the expansion of LoanCore Capital's commercial mortgage origination activities. LoanCore Capital, LLC was formed by Mark Finerman in July 2008 as a real estate asset management and origination platform. LoanCore manages a $1.5 billion commercial real estate debt investment fund in which GIC RE (through an affiliate) had invested in.  This fund focuses exclusively on the acquisition of existing commercial real estate debt. Senior management has originated over $100 billion in commercial mortgages and averages in excess of 20 years of experience in the commercial mortgage finance markets. JLC is headquartered in Greenwich, CT with offices in
Irvine, Los Angeles, San Francisco, Chicago and Atlanta.

Senior Management

JLC's senior management team is led by its Chief Executive Officer, Mark Finerman, who is joined by other senior members of the former RBS team, including Perry Gershon, Chief Investment Officer, and Chris McCormack, Chief Operating Officer.










Mark Finerman
President, Chief Executive Officer

                            Mark Finerman is the President of LoanCore Capital and the CEO of Jefferies
LoanCore. Mr. Finerman founded LoanCore in June 2008.  ... 


Mark Finerman
President, Chief Executive Officer
Mark Finerman is the President of LoanCore Capital and the CEO of Jefferies
LoanCore. Mr. Finerman founded LoanCore in June 2008.  He also serves as
Chairman of the Investment Committee. Mr. Finerman has 25 years of
experience in commercial real estate finance. Prior to forming LoanCore, Mr.
Finerman served as the North American Head of Real Estate Finance and
Securitization at RBS Greenwich Capital from 2002 to 2007. During his tenure,
RBS was named Bank of the Year by Real Estate Finance and Investment, a
publication of Institutional Investor, Inc. Prior to joining RBS, Mr. Finerman served as Head of Estate Finance 
Finance and Securitization at Credit Suisse First Boston (Credit Suisse). From March 1993 to May 1996, Mr.
Finerman was a Director and initial member of the Commercial Real Estate Finance Group at
Nomura Securities International. Mr. Finerman began his career in 1988 at Sun America, where
he was responsible for whole loan originations and trading. He is a graduate of the University of
California, Berkeley where he received a Bachelor of Arts degree in Social Sciences and
received his Masters in Finance from the Marshall School of Business at the University of
Southern California.

More>















Perry Gershon
Chief Investment Officer

                            Mr. Gershon joined LoanCore in June 2008 and is the Chief Investment Officer of Jefferies LoanCore LLC. Prior to joining LoanCore, ... 


Perry Gershon
Chief Investment Officer
Mr. Gershon joined LoanCore in June 2008 and is the Chief Investment Officer of Jefferies LoanCore LLC. Prior to joining LoanCore, Mr. Gershon worked with Mr. Finerman in the Real Estate Finance Group at RBS Greenwich Capital from 2002 to 2008, most recently as Head of Structured Finance. Prior to joining RBS, Mr. Gershon founded the Commercial Real Estate Finance Group at CDC Capital (now Natixis) and served as a Managing Director and Department Head from 1999 to 2000. From 1993 to 1998, Mr. Gershon was a Managing Director and initial member of the Commercial Real Estate Finance Group at Nomura Securities International. Mr. Gershon graduated from Yale University with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Molecular Biophysics and Biochemistry. He received a Master of Business Administration degree from the Haas School of Business at the University of California, Berkeley.

More>







Christopher McCormack
Chief Operating Officer

                            Mr. McCormack joined LoanCore in June of 2008 and is the Chief Operating Officer of Jefferies LoanCore LLC. Prior to joining ... 


Christopher McCormack
Chief Operating Officer
Mr. McCormack joined LoanCore in June of 2008 and is the Chief Operating Officer of Jefferies LoanCore LLC. Prior to joining LoanCore, Mr. McCormack worked in the Real Estate Finance Group at RBS Greenwich Capital from 1998 to 2008, most recently as Head of Capital Markets responsible for overseeing new issue CMBS syndication, secondary trading and structuring. In that role, Mr. McCormack helped develop and build the GG program as well as launched a GNMA project loan business. Mr. McCormack began his career at RBS as a Vice President responsible for structuring and later moved into a trading role. Prior to joining RBS, Mr. McCormack worked as a bond structurer at Donaldson, Lufkin and Jenrette from 1995 to 1998 and Deloitte and Touche from 1992 to 1995. Mr. McCormack graduated from the College of the Holy Cross with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics. He received both a Master of Science degree in Accounting and a Master of Business Administration degree from Northeastern University. Mr. McCormack received his CPA license in 1993 (currently idle) and has Series 7, Series 63 and Series 24 licenses.

More>







Dan Bennett
Head of Capital Markets

                            Mr. Bennett joined LoanCore in 2014 and is the Head of Capital Markets of Jefferies LoanCore LLC. Prior to joining LoanCore, ... 


Dan Bennett
Head of Capital Markets
Mr. Bennett joined LoanCore in 2014 and is the Head of Capital Markets of Jefferies LoanCore LLC. Prior to joining LoanCore, Mr. Bennett worked in the Real Estate Financing Group at Goldman Sachs from 2005 to 2014, most recently as a Managing Director and the Head of the REFG Capital Markets Desk, where he was responsible for the distribution and risk management of the commercial real estate loan book for all new issue CMBS deals and CRE loan syndications. Prior to joining Goldman Sachs, Mr. Bennett was an attorney for Sullivan & Cromwell LLP. Mr. Bennett graduated with a B.S. from Villanova University and with a J.D. from Harvard Law School.

More>




















